result.reason: Server-side RDP limitation — Windows 2012 R2+ throttles concurrent pending connections via MaxOutstandingConnections registry value; not an mRemoteNG client bug
result.approach: This is a Windows Server configuration issue, not an mRemoteNG bug. Users should increase HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Terminal Server\MaxOutstandingConnections on target servers. A potential future enhancement could add connection queuing/throttling in mRemoteNG, but the root cause is server-side.
